he's a dyed-in-the-wool
hophead.

25:07.840 --> 25:09.717
I have a weakness for opium.

25:09.800 --> 25:12.144
That's a habit
that's hard to quit.

25:12.219 --> 25:16.474
Some are born to fail.
Others have it thrust upon them.

25:16.557 --> 25:18.980
Could I see your hands?

25:21.228 --> 25:25.153
Oh. No protruding
knuckles.

25:27.484 --> 25:29.953
No calcium deposits.
Mm-hmm.

25:30.029 --> 25:33.249
Make a fist. Ooh.

25:33.323 --> 25:37.920
More area to absorb the concussion
of a blow without breaking.

25:37.995 --> 25:40.373
Simple matter
of engineering stress.

25:40.456 --> 25:43.881
Reasonably thick skin.
<i>Oh, he's got good skin.</i>

25:43.959 --> 25:47.509
I'd say there's a good
chance you're not...

25:47.588 --> 25:51.138
what Speed, with an unfortunate turn
of phrase, refers to as "a bleeder."

25:51.258 --> 25:54.512
<i>Like I told you, he's good.</i>
How much?

25:54.595 --> 25:58.225
<i>Ten percent of what we
win, expenses. Standard.</i>

26:15.616 --> 26:18.460
Uh, hi.
Mr. Le Beau here?

26:38.639 --> 26:41.768
I need a, uh, short-termer
for a thousand.

26:41.850 --> 26:43.852
Huh. That's
a heavy taste.

26:43.977 --> 26:46.321
How short?
Oh, a day, maybe two.

26:46.396 --> 26:48.524
I've done business
with you before.

26:48.649 --> 26:52.745
Yeah. 'Bout a year ago.
Mm-hmm.

26:52.820 --> 26:58.623
- Got your money back.
- Yeah. You paid back my $300 all right.

26:58.700 --> 27:01.123
But you had to borrow it
from Abboar to do it.

27:01.203 --> 27:04.127
<i>That one you didn't
cover so well.</i>

27:04.206 --> 27:07.585
- Three weeks over. Big deal.
- It was closer to three months.

27:07.668 --> 27:10.091
Well, he got paid.
What's the difference?

27:12.381 --> 27:15.430
Well, there's a big difference
between me and Abboar.

27:16.760 --> 27:19.684
Well, I'll, uh,
take your word for that.

27:23.058 --> 27:25.060
Okay, Speed.

27:27.437 --> 27:30.281
- That's 950.
- I said a thousand.

27:30.357 --> 27:33.452
That's 50 for the loan.

27:33.527 --> 27:35.825
And 50 for every day
until it comes back.

27:37.531 --> 27:41.502
Whew. Boy, you really
puttin' the Jesse James to me.

28:01.638 --> 28:03.982
Now, you wait here, huh?

28:11.732 --> 28:13.655
Well, how long you gonna be?

28:13.734 --> 28:15.657
'Cause I don't feel like
sittin' out here all day.

28:15.736 --> 28:18.114
Listen. Don't start
complaining now.

28:18.197 --> 28:20.666
Don't you get caught up in any
kind of game in there, Speed.

28:20.741 --> 28:23.540
Business.
It's business.

28:25.954 --> 28:28.082
Give me one.

28:31.084 --> 28:33.052
Well, hello, Speed.
Good seein' you, Chick.

28:33.128 --> 28:35.130
How's my personal pigeon?

28:35.214 --> 28:37.137
Just stopped by
to pay off my marker.

28:37.257 --> 28:41.512
Well, that's all right now.
We all make mistakes.

28:41.595 --> 28:44.474
<i>- Guess you heard about my new hitter?
- I'll see that.</i>

28:44.598 --> 28:47.021
Uh, yeah. Word gets around.
Oh, he's good.

28:47.100 --> 28:47.785
Yeah?

28:47.811 --> 28:50.550
Yeah. Might even work him
up to ape man over there.

28:50.604 --> 28:53.198
Well, now, there's-
there's no mystery about it.

28:53.273 --> 28:56.197
It's my standard deal.
But, uh, you see,

28:56.276 --> 28:58.199
you do have to have
a thousand dollars up front.

28:58.278 --> 29:00.872
You makin' an offer?

29:00.948 --> 29:03.167
Well, my man's just startin' out.

29:03.242 --> 29:05.745
He's good, but I have to get long
odds if I'm gonna face skinhead.

29:05.827 --> 29:11.084
Assuming that you did have the money,
what kind of odds you talkin' about?

29:12.125 --> 29:15.720
- Five to one.
- Three to one.

29:17.965 --> 29:22.391
Deal
Somebody die and leave it to ya?

29:22.469 --> 29:24.563
Three to one, Chickie. Money's
on the table. What do ya say?

29:24.638 --> 29:26.936
You know, I don't like being hustled
by a hope-and-a-prayer artist.

29:27.015 --> 29:29.143
<i>You're not gettin'
in that cheap.</i>

29:29.226 --> 29:32.105
The pot bet just now
went up to three thousand.

29:32.187 --> 29:35.817
<i>Now, you come on back,
when you get that rich.</i>

29:35.899 --> 29:40.405
- You mean to tell me we don't have a deal?
- Not for a thousand.

29:44.992 --> 29:47.541
I'll see you soon, Dempsey.

29:58.005 --> 30:00.929
<i>I'm feelin' quite fine,
Mr. Pettibon. Quite fine.</i>

30:01.008 --> 30:04.808
Well, listen, we got a boy down here I think
could make an interesting contest for you.

30:06.930 --> 30:10.355
Well, now, that's, uh,
quite a bit of money.

30:11.977 --> 30:15.527
I don't know whether our boy's up
to it or not. He's just startin' out.

30:15.605 --> 30:17.653
He's, uh, real game.
He's awful green though.

30:19.484 --> 30:21.782
<i>Nobody takes advantage
of you bayou people.</i>

30:23.155 --> 30:27.376
We'll be there, Mr. Pettibon.
Good talkin' with ya.

30:29.870 --> 30:31.793
Told you it'd be a fat one.

30:31.872 --> 30:33.874
Barber-
How high?

30:35.542 --> 30:38.591
